... 72 \nFigure 70: Exports reductions in HASP ... 73 \nFigure 71: CAISO daily total and average market costs ... 74 \nFigure 72: Real-time energy and congestion offsets for CAISO ... 75 \nFigure 73: Real-time energy and congestion offsets for WEIM ... 75 \nFigure 74: Off-peak next-day power price at Western hubs ... 76 \nFigure 75: Off-peak future power prices for January and February 2024 ... 76 \nFigure 76. Percentage of capacity up failures per BAA ... 77 \nFigure 77: Percentage of capacity down failures per BAA ... 78 \nFigure 78: Percentage of flexible ramping up failures per BAA ... 78 \nFigure 79: Percentage of flexible ramping down failures per BAA ... 79 \nFigure 80: Day-ahead demand forecast for WEIM Footprint ... 80 \n\nAcronyms \nAET Assistance Energy Transfer \nAZPS Arizona Public Service \nBAA Balancing Authority Area \nBANC Balancing Authority of Northern California \nCAISO California Independent System Operator \nDAM Day ahead market \nDLAP Default Load Aggregated Point \nDSW Desert Southwest \nEEA \nEIM \n\nEnergy Emergency Alert Energy Imbalance Market EPE El Paso Electric ETC Existing Transmission Contract F Fahrenheit FMM Fifteen Minute Market HASP Hour Ahead Scheduling Process HE Hour Ending IFM Integrated Forward Market IID Imperial Irrigation District IPCO Idaho Power Company LADWP Los Angeles Department of Water and Power LESR Limited Energy Storage Resource LMP Locational Marginal Price\n\nLPT\n\nLow priority export. This is a scheduling priority assigned to price-taker exports that do not have a non-RA supporting resource LSE Load Serving Entity MAPE Mean Absolute Percentage Error MNW Mountain Northwest MW Megawatt MWh Megawatt-hour NEVP or NVE NV Energy\n\nNGR Non-Generating Resource \nNOB Nevada-Oregon Border \nNSI Net Scheduled Interchange \nNWMT Northwestern Energy \nOASIS Open Access Same-Time Information System \nOR Operating Reserves \nPACE PacifiCorp East \nPACW PacifiCorp West \nPGE Portland General Electric \nPNM Public Service C